# names of variables to exclude

  select(starts_with("neuro_")) %>% 
  select(-c(neuro_tbiMild, neuro_oth, neuro_oth_text)) %>%

df.neuro = df %>% select(neuroNames)

##              31              12              17               5
# column indices of variables to exclude 
neuroIndices = which(names(df) %in% neuroNames)

# initialize vector of subjects with neuro conditions 
neuroSubjects = vector(mode = "character")

## if subject responded Yes to any neuro condition, 
## add their row number to neuroSubject
for (row in 1:nrow(df)) {
  for (col in 1:length(neuroIndices)) {
    if (df[row, neuroIndices[col]] == "Yes") {
      neuroSubjects = append(neuroSubjects, row)
    }
  }
}

## manually add subjects to exclusion list based on "other" responses

Custom functions

# MLM effect sizes (semi-partial R squared)
calculateRsq = function(dfNum, dfDen, Fval) {
  Rsq = ((dfNum / dfDen) * Fval) / (1 + (dfNum / dfDen) * Fval) 
  print(Rsq)
}

Is age associated with objective performance on memory and cognitive tasks?

Face-name associative memory

model_age.fn = 
  lmer(fn_score ~ age * fn_domain + (1|subjectID),
       data = df.fn.long)

omnibus_age.fn = anova(model_age.fn, ddf = "Satterthwaite", type = 3)

omnibus_age.fn$Rsq = 
  calculateRsq(omnibus_age.fn$NumDF, 
               omnibus_age.fn$DenDF, 
               omnibus_age.fn$`F value`)
